<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>A rectangular <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType"><rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> shaft</rs> (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">1.21</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.60</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.575</measure>); panels within moulding on four sides (<measure dim="width" type="length" unit="metre">0.40</measure> x <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.98</measure>).</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on two opposite faces within the panels.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Description of Letters</head>
<p>i. Unpublished. ii.  <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.03-0.04</measure>; <foreign lang="grc">Φ</foreign>, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.055</measure>; elongated and clear cut; similar to <xref type="inscription" n="20" href="080405">8.405</xref>; scroll for abbreviation.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p><date precision="circa" value="0364" notBefore="0364" notAfter="0364" exact="both">A.D. 364</date> (<rs type="criteria">reign</rs>).</p>
</div>

<div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<div type="textpart_section" n="ii"><ab><lb n="1"/><persName key="Valens" type="emperor" full="yes"><name reg="Φλάβιος"><expan><abbr>Φλ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">άουιον</supplied></expan></name> <name reg="Κλαύδιος"><expan><abbr>Κλ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">αύδιον</supplied></expan></name> <name reg="Βάλης">Βάλητα</name></persName><lb n="2"/><space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/> <rs type="dignity" key="augustus">Αὔγουστον</rs><lb n="3"/><persName type="aphrodisian" key="TatianusAnt" full="yes"><name reg="Ἀντώνιος"><expan><abbr>Ἀντ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ώνιος</supplied></expan></name> <name reg="Τατιανός">Τατιανὸς</name></persName><lb n="4"/><w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w> <rs type="dignity" key="clarissimus"><w lemma="λαμπρός"><expan><abbr>λαμπρ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ότατος</supplied></expan></w></rs> <rs type="official-secul" key="praeses"><w lemma="ἡγεμών">ἡγεμὼν</w></rs><lb n="5"/><rs type="admin" key="Caria"><w lemma="ἐπαρχεία">ἐπαρχείας</w><lb n="6"/><space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/> <placeName reg="Καρία">Καρίας</placeName></rs> <g type="leaf"/>
</ab></div>
</div>

<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p> Antonius Tatianos, <term lang="la">clarissimus praeses</term> of the province of Caria <supplied reason="subaudible">set up this statue of</supplied> Flavius Claudius Valens, Augustus.</p>
</div>

<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>i. No commentary yet (2007)</p><p>ii. See discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="III.10">III.10</xref>.</p>
</div>

<div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p> <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList" key="Theatre">Theatre</rs>: re-used in the central stretch of the Theatre defence wall.</rs> <rs type="origLocation">re-used in the <rs type="monuList" key="Tetrastoon">Tetrastoon</rs>, west portico in the fourth century: a rectangular plinth, on which this base probably stood, is in position, against a column of the west portico of the tetrastoon, just south of the probable plinth of <xref type="inscription" n="20" href="080405">8.405</xref>. .</rs>. Last recorded location: <rs type="lastLocation">Museum (2004).</rs>. </p></div>




<div type="history" n="record">
<head>History of Recording</head>
<p>Excavated in 1972 by the NYU expedition (<rs type="invNo">72.54</rs>).</p>
</div>

<div type="bibliography" n="none_i">
<head>Bibliography</head>
<p>i. Unpublished. ii. cited by <bibl><author>J. R. Martindale</author>, <title level="j">Historia</title> 29 (<date value="1980" notBefore="1980" notAfter="1980" exact="both">1980</date>), 494</bibl>; published by <bibl type="hbi" rend="primary" n="ALA"><author>Roueché</author>, <title level="m">Aphrodisias in Late Antiquity</title> no. <biblScope>21</biblScope>  and Plate vi</bibl>, whence <bibl n="PHI"><author>McCabe</author> <title level="m">PHI Aphrodisias</title> <biblScope n="257541">658</biblScope></bibl>.</p>
</div>

